  <title translate="true">System Folder Summary</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">System Folder</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is both the entry point and the hub of the </text><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%APP%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> development environment. It displays a number of icons &#160;that can be used to launch the various development tools. The folder also contains sub-folders (such as </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Additional Tools</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Samples</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">) holding further, less commonly used, icons within them.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">You can use </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Help/What&apos;s This?</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> (Shift+F1) inside </text><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%APP%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to get a brief description of each of the tool icons.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Notes"><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">System Folder</text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true"> is implemented by the </text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">SmalltalkSystemShell</text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true"> class in the image.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
